OneShotFastECPP -- installation
===============================

Everything builds and runs *inside the project tree*; nothing is written to
/usr/local or installed system-wide.


1. Dependencies
---------------
  * gcc  13 or newer          (C11, OpenMP, __int128, -march=native)
  * GMP  6 or newer           (libgmp, with headers)
  * make
  * PARI/GP 2.x               -- ONLY for the correctness test suites; the
                                 oneshot certificate generator does NOT need it.
  * python3                   -- for the test scripts and to run voneshot.py.

  On Debian/Ubuntu:
      sudo apt-get install build-essential libgmp-dev pari-gp python3


2. Build
--------
  From the repository root:

      make -j

  This does four things, in order:
    (a) builds ff_poly_v2.0.0 and stages it into ./local  (a project-local prefix),
    (b) builds classpoly_v1.0.3 against ./local,
    (c) builds zp_poly (large-p F_p[x] library; used by classpoly's invariant->j
        conversion) and stages it into ./local,
    (d) builds the ecpp/ tools (oneshot, cm_method, dscan, smoothtest, roottest, ...)
        against classpoly's headers/objects and ./local.

  Clean:      make clean
  Full clean: make distclean          (also removes ./local and ./work)


3. Environment
--------------
  Before running the tools, source the environment file once per shell:

      . ./setenv.sh

  It sets CLASSPOLY_PHI_DIR to the bundled ./phi_files, sets an output directory
  (CLASSPOLY_H_DIR = ./work/H_files), and puts ./classpoly_v1.0.3 and ./ecpp on
  PATH so the tools can find classpoly, dscan, cm_method, etc.


4. Run
------
      ./ecpp/oneshot p=<decimal-prime>
      ./ecpp/oneshot pbits=256 seed=1              # a random 256-bit prime
      ./ecpp/oneshot p=... threads=16 c=1 B=1e10   # all knobs (see README)

  The smoothness bound climbs a power-of-2 ladder starting just above n^2
  (n = bitlength(p)): prime-product segments are built on demand and cached in
  work/pcache/ (segments are bit-length independent, so every prime size shares
  them), the discriminant-scan bound widens geometrically in between, and the
  run stops at the first rung that yields a certificate.  Cold first runs cost
  seconds at 256 bits; the c= knob (default 1) sets how much testing work must
  accumulate before the next segment is built.
  Output is one line "p A x0 m q1 ... qk"; verify with voneshot.py from
  https://github.com/AndrewVSutherland/OneShotPrimalityProofs .


5. Modular polynomials (phi_files/)
-----------------------------------
  Computing H_D mod p needs modular polynomials.  We bundle a 46 MB subset (the
  files in phi_files_manifest.txt): for EVERY class-invariant family f, the
  enumeration polynomials Phi_{l,f} for primes l <= 71 and the invariant->j
  polynomial Psi_f.  The classical polynomials Phi_l (phi_j_* files) fall under
  the same rule; they are not used for enumeration (an invariant better than j is
  always chosen) but ARE needed at the primes dividing the LEVEL of the chosen
  invariant -- e.g. phi_j_59 when Atkin A_59 is picked -- to derive the starting
  f-value from the starting j-invariant (see Enge-Sutherland, "Class invariants
  by the CRT method", Lemma on Psi_f roots), plus phi_j_2 for 2-volcano
  orientation.  l <= 71 covers every level and enumeration prime observed across
  extensive traces (128-384-bit p, |D| up to 10^10).

  This is sufficient for oneshot in that range: if a particular discriminant needs
  a modular polynomial that is not bundled, classpoly reports it and oneshot simply
  tries the next smoothness winner.  For the full database of modular polynomials
  (all levels, ~2.2 GB), see A. Sutherland's modular polynomial database; drop the
  files into phi_files/ (or point CLASSPOLY_PHI_DIR elsewhere).


6. Tests (optional, need PARI/GP)
---------------------------------
      make test                     # classpoly vs PARI over |D| <= 1000 (~2.5 min)
      python3 ecpp/test_dscan.py    # CM-discriminant scan vs PARI + brute force
      python3 ecpp/test_smooth.py   # n^4-smoothness engine vs PARI
      ./ecpp/roottest pari 256 200  # big-F_p root finder vs PARI polrootsmod
